  "local_port": 34544,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What's the best applicant tracking system for a small staffing agency?",
  "response": "Choosing the best applicant tracking system (ATS) for a small staffing agency depends on various factors, including your specific needs, budget, and the size of your team. Here are some top ATS options that are well-suited for small staffing agencies:\n\n1. **BambooHR**:\n   - **Pros**: User-friendly, great for small businesses, integrates well with other HR tools, and has an affordable price point.\n   - **Cons**: May lack some advanced features that larger agencies might need.\n\n2. **JazzHR**:\n   - **Pros**: Scalable for small to medium-sized businesses, offers a good balance of features and affordability, and has a user-friendly interface.\n   - **Cons**: Some users find the customer support lacking at times.\n\n3. **Workable**:\n   - **Pros**: Easy to use, offers robust reporting and analytics, integrates well with other tools, and has a good mobile app.\n   - **Cons**: Can be pricey for the smallest agencies, though it often offers discounts for startups.\n\n4. **Zoho Recruit**:\n   - **Pros**: Highly customizable, integrates well with other Zoho products, and offers a free plan for small teams.\n   - **Cons**: The interface can be overwhelming for new users, and some advanced features are only available in higher-tier plans.\n\n5. **Crelate**:\n   - **Pros**: Specifically designed for staffing and recruiting agencies, offers a good balance of features and affordability, and has a user-friendly interface.\n   - **Cons**: Some users find the initial setup process a bit complex.\n\n6. **Bullhorn**:\n   - **Pros**: Industry leader in staffing and recruiting software, offers powerful features and good integration options.\n   - **Cons**: Can be expensive and may be more than what a very small agency needs.\n\nWhen choosing an ATS, consider the following key factors:\n\n- **Ease of Use**: How intuitive is the interface? Will your team be able to quickly adapt to it?\n- **Features**: Does it offer the features you need, such as job posting, resume parsing, candidate tracking, and reporting?\n- **Integration**: Can it integrate with other tools you use, like email, calendars, and HR systems?\n- **Cost**: Is it within your budget? Are there additional fees for extra users or features?\n- **Customer Support**: What kind of support does the provider offer? Is it available when you need it?\n- **Scalability**: Will the ATS grow with your business, or will you need to switch to another system as you expand?\n\nFor a small staffing agency, **JazzHR** or **Zoho Recruit** might be the best starting points due to their balance of features, ease of use, and affordability. However, it's worth exploring demos and free trials of a few options to see which one best fits your specific needs.",
